.SS jobs
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl jobs [\[en]json] list\f[R]
Background Tasks runtime (jobs-api :8142) \[em] the long-running work
the box runs OFF the request path: a background CoAT deliberation, a
model eval, a secondary-model load, a GPU job, or a job mirrored from
the RTX-4090 VM.
list / status are read-only; submit / cancel are the ACTIONS the cockpit
routes through control-exec-api.
Rendered live in the Code Console\[cq]s Background Tasks pane.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl jobs [\[en]json] status \f[R]
Additional supported form.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl jobs [\[en]json] submit deliberation \[en]problem \[lq]\&...\[rq] [\[en]rung coat]\f[R]
Additional supported form.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl jobs [\[en]json] submit eval \[en] python3 scripts/models/eval.py \&...\f[R]
Additional supported form.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl jobs [\[en]json] cancel \f[R]
Additional supported form.
## plane
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl plane\f[R]
The Sovereign Compute Plane (via jobs-api :8142) \[em] the box\[cq]s
devices with LIVE free VRAM + the outstanding claims (model residents +
running GPU jobs), placed by the M075 SRP doctrine.
Read-only.
A GPU job is placed on a device that fits, or waits, so it never OOMs
the box.
